Sew Green, Basic Sewing Series
description:
SEW GREEN is a Basic sewing class taught by independent designer Hekima Hapa of HarrietsbyHekima formerly Harriets Alter Ego.

 

Sew Green is for the sewing novice who envisions reconstructing vintage and existing wardrobe or tackling simple home décor projects.
 The class is offered in four, two hour sessions. The class fee of $125 includes all materials and basic sewing kit for each student. Sewing kits includes scissors, seam ripper, tape measure, straight pins & pin cushion. 

 

****** STUDENTS MUST PROVIDE OWN SEWING MACHINES.********


Course work includes: 
Threading Techniques
Seams, Hems & Proper Ironing
Elastics & Drawstrings
Gathers & Pleats
 Zippers
Buttons & Button Holes
Completion of 1 project

 

Next session  Sunday January 5, 12, 19 & 26

@ Harriets Full Circle Boutique 776 St. Johns Street, Brooklyn

10am-noon  Space is limited to 10 students per session.
